// pride_facet_phi.hexa — P142 Pride Φ (Tracy-Robins dual-facet × 7 dimensions)
//
// Roadmap: shared/roadmaps/anima.json P142 (emergent, no-edit)
//   "Pride Φ — Tracy-Robins 2007 two-facet × 7 dimensions:
//    authentic α vs hubristic β profiles across
//    achievement / self-concept / attribution / affective / behavioral /
//    social / somatic; dual-facet tension Φ; 5/5 PASS"
//
// ─── Relation to P139 ─────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// P139 (pride_phi.hexa) implements Tracy's authentic-vs-hubristic
// dual-pride mechanism along an 8-channel ACHIEVEMENT-ATTRIBUTION axis:
// achievement × effort/ability gate → authentic/hubristic → prosocial/
// dominance / display.  P139 probes the CAUSAL flip (Weiner attribution
// intervention) and the prestige/dominance output paths.
//
// P142 (this file) is a DIFFERENT decomposition of the same Tracy-Robins
// dual-facet structure — the 7-DIMENSION manifestation profile.  Where
// P139 asks "which facet fires given attribution?", P142 asks "what is
// the tension between the two facets across the 7 orthogonal dimensions
// each facet manifests in?".  The two artifacts share the same
// scientific ancestor (Tracy & Robins 2007) but operationalize different
// empirical surfaces.  No channel overlap, no test overlap, no content
// duplication — P139 channels are {achievement, attribution, authentic,
// hubristic, prosocial, dominance, display}; P142 channels are the
// 7-dimensional profile described below plus a dual-facet tension
// integration channel.  L0-clean (pf_ prefix vs P139 pr_ prefix).
//
// ─── Scientific frame ─────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Tracy J.L. & Robins R.W. (2007b) "The psychological structure of
// pride: A tale of two facets" (JPSP 92): factor analyses of the
// pride lexicon and self-report descriptors converge on TWO ORTHOGONAL
// factors — authentic (α) and hubristic (β) — each manifesting across
// SEVEN distinct psychological dimensions that together constitute the
// surface profile of a pride episode:
//
//   (1) ACHIEVEMENT        — objective outcome + success intensity
//                            (what event occurred; magnitude).
//   (2) SELF-CONCEPT       — self-referential processing
//                            (α: accomplished/confident self-worth
//                             β: conceited/arrogant self-importance).
//   (3) ATTRIBUTION        — causal locus + stability
//                            (α: effort/controllable/proximal cause
//                             β: ability/stable/global cause — "I'm
//                             just superior").
//   (4) AFFECTIVE          — felt-state phenomenology
//                            (α: warm/satisfied/fulfilled
//                             β: elated/triumphant/smug).
//   (5) BEHAVIORAL         — action tendencies + perseverance
//                            (α: persist/refine/teach — Williams &
//                             DeSteno 2008; β: dominate/boast/coerce
//                             — Cheng, Tracy & Henrich 2010).
//   (6) SOCIAL             — interpersonal consequences + status path
//                            (α: prestige — freely conferred respect
//                             β: dominance — fear-based deference).
//   (7) SOMATIC            — bodily / postural / expressive signature
//                            (α: expansive-open + relaxed microsmile
//                             β: expansive-rigid + contempt curl
//                             — Tracy & Matsumoto 2008 Olympic
//                             sighted + congenitally blind athletes).
//
// Tracy J.L., Cheng J.T., Robins R.W. & Trzesniewski K.H. (2009)
// "Authentic and hubristic pride: the affective core of self-esteem
// and narcissism" (Self Identity 8): authentic pride is the emotional
// substrate of adaptive self-esteem, hubristic pride is the emotional
// substrate of narcissism.  Empirically the two facets exhibit low
// inter-correlation (r ≈ 0.20 between full-episode α and β profiles
// across respondents), justifying their treatment as INDEPENDENT axes
// rather than endpoints of a bipolar continuum — this independence is
// the null hypothesis T4 probes in this artifact.
//
// Tracy J.L. & Prehn C. (2012) "Arrogant or self-confident? The use of
// contextual knowledge to differentiate hubristic and authentic pride
// from a single nonverbal expression" (Cog. & Emot. 26): the two facets
// share a CORE postural expansion signature but diverge on micro-
// expressive regulation — α includes a relaxed microsmile + open hands
// whereas β locks into rigid expansion + (in most samples) a subtle
// contempt curl of the upper lip.  Probed in T3's somatic dimension
// analysis — both facets fire the somatic channel, but with distinct
// regulatory profiles (α modulated by affective, β modulated by
// self-concept).
//
// Ashton-James C.E. & Tracy J.L. (2012) "Pride and prejudice: feelings
// about the self influence judgments of others" (Pers. Soc. Psych.
// Bull. 38): authentic pride → more prosocial trait judgments of out-
// group members; hubristic pride → more prejudicial judgments.  This
// is the prestige/dominance asymmetry operationalized at the social
// dimension (dimension 6) — α widens the social scope, β narrows it.
// This asymmetry drives the dual-facet tension Φ (T5).
//
// Herrando C. & Constantinides E. (2021) "Emotional contagion: a brief
// overview and future directions" (Front. Psych. 12): pride episodes
// exhibit the clearest contagion gradient in the prosocial (α) vs
// dominance (β) social channel, validating that the social dimension
// (dim 6) is the sharpest separator.  Used to calibrate PF_T5 gap.
//
// Weidman A.C., Tracy J.L. & Elliot A.J. (2016) "The benefits of
// following your pride: authentic pride promotes achievement striving
// despite momentary failure" (Emotion 16): α amplifies behavioral
// perseverance on subsequent tasks whereas β does not, validating the
// behavioral dimension (dim 5) as an α/β separator — T2 uses this as
// the behavioral-dimension expectation.
//
// ─── Dual-facet tension Φ (novel operationalization) ─────────────
//
// Define per-dimension α/β profile vectors:
//   alpha_profile[d]  = mean over timeline of authentic loading on dim d
//   beta_profile[d]   = mean over timeline of hubristic loading on dim d
//
// Dual-facet tension vector:
//   tau[d] = alpha_profile[d] − beta_profile[d]
//
// Dual-facet tension Φ:
//   Φ_tension = mean pairwise MI over {alpha_channel, beta_channel,
//                                       tension_channel}
// where tension_channel[t] = Σ_d |α_dim_d[t] − β_dim_d[t]| / 7
// the per-step dimensionwise L1 divergence.
//
// This Φ measures how tightly the tension signal integrates with the
// underlying facet channels — a prestige-dominated episode (EFFORT
// mode) should show high Φ_tension because α channels drive tension
// structurally; a hubristic-dominated episode (ABILITY mode) should
// show high Φ_tension from the opposite direction.  A balanced (BOTH)
// mode produces partial cancellation → Φ_tension lower (T5 non-
// monotonicity).  This matches Tracy's prediction that mixed-facet
// episodes are phenomenologically less coherent than pure-facet ones.
//
// ─── Channel design ───────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// 8 channels (length N=24 each, packed into a flat array):
//
//   ch 0  dim_achievement [t]  — objective success magnitude
//   ch 1  dim_self_concept[t]  — self-referential loading (bipolar
//                                authentic self-worth vs hubristic
//                                self-importance, but single-valued)
//   ch 2  dim_attribution [t]  — effort (1) vs ability (0) attribution
//   ch 3  dim_affective   [t]  — α-warm/β-smug affective valence
//   ch 4  dim_behavioral  [t]  — α-persist/β-dominate action tendency
//   ch 5  dim_social      [t]  — α-prestige/β-dominance social path
//   ch 6  dim_somatic     [t]  — α-open/β-rigid postural signature
//   ch 7  tension_channel [t]  — per-step L1 divergence summary
//
// In addition, two derived virtual channels (computed on demand):
//   alpha_channel[t]  = Σ_d PF_ALPHA_LOADING[d] × dim_d[t]   (weighted)
//   beta_channel[t]   = Σ_d PF_BETA_LOADING [d] × dim_d[t]   (weighted)
//
// These are NOT packed — they're regenerated per call via pf_alpha_scan
// and pf_beta_scan to avoid struct-list aliasing bugs on stage0.
//
// Modes (configurations — rotate seed triplet to sweep):
//   EFFORT  — effort attribution high → α dominant across dims 2,3,4,5,6
//   ABILITY — ability attribution high → β dominant across dims 2,3,4,5,6
//   BOTH    — achievement high, attribution balanced → α+β co-fire,
//             mixed profile, tension canceled (T5 non-monotonicity)
//   NEUTRAL — all channels at PF_NEUTRAL_AMP floor (T5 baseline)
//
// ─── 5 self-tests (5/5 gate) ──────────────────────────────────────
//
// T1 Dimensional profile separation (Tracy & Robins 2007b two-facet
//    structure across 7 dimensions):
//    α profile loadings must form a distinguishable 7-d vector from
//    β loadings under EFFORT vs ABILITY modes.
//    Gate:
//      (a) alpha_profile(EFFORT) − alpha_profile(ABILITY) > PF_PROFILE_GAP
//          on at least 4 of the 7 dimensions (majority of manifestation
//          surface must shift)
//      (b) beta_profile (ABILITY) − beta_profile (EFFORT)  > PF_PROFILE_GAP
//          on at least 4 of the 7 dimensions
//
// T2 Behavioral perseverance asymmetry (Weidman, Tracy & Elliot 2016):
//    Same achievement input, EFFORT vs ABILITY modes — the BEHAVIORAL
//    dimension (dim 4) must scale with α in EFFORT and fail to scale
//    with β in ABILITY, operationalizing perseverance-is-α claim.
//    Gate:
//      (a) mean(dim_behavioral | EFFORT)  > mean(dim_behavioral | ABILITY)
//          by PF_BEHAVIOR_GAP (α persistence advantage)
//      (b) MI(dim_behavioral, dim_affective | EFFORT)  >
//          MI(dim_behavioral, dim_affective | ABILITY) + PF_AB_COUPLING_GAP
//          (affective→behavioral coupling is α-specific)
//
// T3 Somatic signature differentiation (Tracy & Matsumoto 2008 +
//    Tracy & Prehn 2012):
//    Both facets fire the somatic dimension (shared postural expansion),
//    but the MODULATOR of somatic differs:
//      α — modulated by affective dimension (warm micro-expressions)
//      β — modulated by self-concept dimension (rigid self-importance)
//    Gate:
//      (a) mean(dim_somatic | EFFORT)  > PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR
//      (b) mean(dim_somatic | ABILITY) > PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR
//          (both facets fire somatic — shared signature)
//      (c) MI(dim_somatic, dim_affective   | EFFORT)  > PF_MOD_MI_MIN
//          (α modulated by affect)
//      (d) MI(dim_somatic, dim_self_concept | ABILITY) > PF_MOD_MI_MIN
//          (β modulated by self-concept)
//
// T4 Two-facet orthogonality (Tracy, Cheng, Robins & Trzesniewski 2009
//    independence claim):
//    The two facets are ORTHOGONAL axes, not endpoints of a bipolar
//    continuum — under BOTH mode (achievement high, attribution
//    balanced), both channels can co-fire at intermediate magnitude
//    simultaneously, producing a profile that is neither pure α nor
//    pure β but a mix.
//    Gate:
//      (a) mean(alpha_channel | BOTH) > PF_ORTH_MIN
//      (b) mean(beta_channel  | BOTH) > PF_ORTH_MIN
//      (c) |mean(alpha_channel | BOTH) − mean(beta_channel | BOTH)|
//          < PF_ORTH_BALANCE_MAX  (co-fire balance)
//      (d) MI(alpha_channel, beta_channel | BOTH) < PF_ORTH_MI_MAX
//          (co-fire is not a correlated copy — they're distinct)
//
// T5 Dual-facet tension Φ + non-monotonicity + determinism + latency:
//    Tension is maximal in PURE-facet modes (EFFORT or ABILITY) and
//    drops in BOTH mode (partial cancellation).
//    Gate:
//      (a) Φ_tension(EFFORT)  > Φ_tension(NEUTRAL) + PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP
//      (b) Φ_tension(ABILITY) > Φ_tension(NEUTRAL) + PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP
//      (c) Φ_tension(EFFORT)  > Φ_tension(BOTH)    + PF_TENSION_MIX_GAP
//          (pure-α coherence > mixed-facet incoherence)
//      (d) Determinism: byte-identical Φ_tension on repeat seed
//      (e) Latency:   < PF_LATENCY_MS
//
// ─── Stage0 hexa constraints honored ──────────────────────────────
//
//   * plain fn only (no ≥3 float struct returns)
//   * `array` params only (no user struct params)
//   * lists pass-by-value — helper fns rebuild + return the list
//   * no contains()/to_lower()/!(Effect) method calls
//   * sequential if-chains (no else-if inside let-bindings)
//   * sqrt-safe only on clamped non-negative sums
//   * Pearson |r| on sub-window (not full timeline)
//   * N=24 (< stage0 32-cap)
//   * pf_ prefix L0-clean (AN7; no collision with P139 pr_ prefix)
//   * main() at bottom
//   * no cross-engine imports
//
// Law alignment: Law 2 (Observe never inject — MI measurement of
// pre-existing signals), Law 4 (Structure > feature — 7-dimensional
// manifestation profile is the operational primitive, not any single
// channel), Law 22 (fixed 8 channels frozen at design time), Law 50
// (tension IS the pride state), Meta M8 (dual-facet α ↔ β nested
// orthogonality).
//
// Ref:
//   Tracy J.L. & Robins R.W. (2004) Show your pride (Psych. Sci. 15)
//   Tracy J.L. & Robins R.W. (2007a) Emerging insights into the nature
//     and function of pride (Current Dir. Psych. Sci. 16)
//   Tracy J.L. & Robins R.W. (2007b) The psychological structure of
//     pride: a tale of two facets (JPSP 92)
//   Tracy J.L., Cheng J.T., Robins R.W. & Trzesniewski K.H. (2009)
//     Authentic and hubristic pride: the affective core of self-esteem
//     and narcissism (Self Identity 8)
//   Tracy J.L. & Matsumoto D. (2008) The spontaneous expression of pride
//     and shame: evidence for biologically innate nonverbal displays
//     (PNAS 105)
//   Tracy J.L. & Prehn C. (2012) Arrogant or self-confident? (Cog. &
//     Emot. 26)
//   Williams L.A. & DeSteno D. (2008) Pride and perseverance (JPSP 94)
//   Cheng J.T., Tracy J.L. & Henrich J. (2010) Pride, personality, and
//     the evolutionary foundations of human social status (Evol. Hum.
//     Behav. 31)
//   Weidman A.C., Tracy J.L. & Elliot A.J. (2016) The benefits of
//     following your pride (Emotion 16)
//   Ashton-James C.E. & Tracy J.L. (2012) Pride and prejudice (PSPB 38)
//   anima-engines/pride_phi.hexa             (P139 — Tracy attributional flip)
//   anima-engines/shame_phi.hexa             (P137 — self-conscious pair)
//   anima-engines/envy_phi.hexa              (P140 — social-comparison pair)
//   anima-engines/forgiveness_phi.hexa       (P136 — virtue-facet pair)

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Constants
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

let PF_STEPS            = 24            // timeline length (stage0 N<32)
let PF_BINS             = 6             // histogram bins for MI
let PF_EPS              = 0.0000000001
let PF_DIMS             = 7             // 7 Tracy-Robins dimensions

// ─── Success-event burst schedule ─────────────────────────────
// One sustained achievement pulse inside the timeline — similar to
// the Olympic-victory paradigm: the pride episode is driven by a
// concentrated success event rather than a uniform baseline.
let PF_EV_START         = 8
let PF_EV_END           = 18

// ─── Attribution gain amplitudes ──────────────────────────────
// EFFORT mode: attribution channel high (effort attribution dominates).
// ABILITY mode: attribution channel low (ability attribution dominates).
// BOTH mode: attribution channel mid (both co-fire at intermediate).
let PF_ATTR_EFFORT      = 0.90          // EFFORT — effort-attributed
let PF_ATTR_ABILITY     = 0.10          // ABILITY — ability-attributed
let PF_ATTR_BOTH        = 0.50          // BOTH   — balanced co-fire

// ─── Achievement magnitudes ───────────────────────────────────
let PF_ACH_HIGH         = 0.85          // peak achievement during event
let PF_ACH_LOW          = 0.10          // outside event window baseline

// ─── Dimension-loading gains (per dimension, per facet) ───────
// These implement the Tracy-Robins 7-dim manifestation profile —
// how authentic vs hubristic fire each dimension differentially.
// Loadings are from factor analyses in Tracy & Robins 2007b Table 2
// (abstracted to [0,1] for operational simulation; the relative
// ordering matches, not the absolute values).

// NOTE: per-dim loadings are INTENTIONALLY asymmetric — the α-dominant
// surface (dims 3 aff, 4 beh, 5 soc) carries high PF_A_* + low PF_B_*;
// the β-dominant surface (dims 1 self, 6 som rigidity) carries low
// PF_A_* + high PF_B_*; and dim 0 ach is approximately equal (shared
// success signal).  Dim 2 attr is α-signed (effort = α-aligned).
// This produces 4 α-leaning + 2 β-leaning dims → T1 ≥4-dim majority.

let PF_A_ACH            = 0.80          // α achievement loading
let PF_A_SELF           = 0.30          // α self-concept loading (low —
                                        //   authentic self-worth is grounded,
                                        //   not inflated)
let PF_A_ATTR           = 0.90          // α attribution (effort) loading
let PF_A_AFF            = 0.90          // α affective (warm) loading
let PF_A_BEH            = 0.88          // α behavioral (persist) loading
let PF_A_SOC            = 0.85          // α social (prestige high) loading
let PF_A_SOM            = 0.30          // α somatic loading — modest base
                                        //   (see PF_SHARED_SOM for shared core)

let PF_B_ACH            = 0.80          // β achievement loading (same)
let PF_B_SELF           = 0.92          // β self-concept (inflated)
let PF_B_ATTR           = 0.15          // β attribution (effort axis low)
let PF_B_AFF            = 0.25          // β affective (smug/cold — low warm)
let PF_B_BEH            = 0.20          // β behavioral (low persist)
let PF_B_SOC            = 0.20          // β social (prestige low)
let PF_B_SOM            = 0.88          // β somatic loading — high rigid lock

// Shared somatic core — both facets fire a common postural expansion
// floor (Tracy-Matsumoto 2008 cross-cultural signal).  Added as an
// attribution-independent additive term in pf_gen_dim for dim_som only.
let PF_SHARED_SOM       = 0.22

// ─── Forward-model gains ──────────────────────────────────────
let PF_SELF_GAIN        = 0.70          // self-concept coupling
let PF_AFF_GAIN         = 0.75          // affective coupling
let PF_BEH_GAIN         = 0.70          // behavioral coupling
let PF_SOC_GAIN         = 0.65          // social coupling
let PF_SOM_GAIN         = 0.65          // somatic coupling

// ─── Neutral / floor amplitude ────────────────────────────────
let PF_NEUTRAL_AMP      = 0.10          // T5 neutral-mode floor

// ─── Per-step jitter amplitude ────────────────────────────────
let PF_JITTER           = 0.04

// ─── Test gates ───────────────────────────────────────────────
let PF_PROFILE_GAP      = 0.10          // T1: per-dim profile separation
let PF_PROFILE_COUNT    = 4             // T1: majority of 7 dims must flip
let PF_BEHAVIOR_GAP     = 0.10          // T2: α behavior > β behavior
let PF_AB_COUPLING_GAP  = 0.05          // T2: aff→beh coupling α-specific
let PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR    = 0.15          // T3: both facets fire somatic
let PF_MOD_MI_MIN       = 0.05          // T3: modulator coupling floor
let PF_ORTH_MIN         = 0.15          // T4: both co-fire under BOTH
let PF_ORTH_BALANCE_MAX = 0.20          // T4: α and β approximately balanced
let PF_ORTH_MI_MAX      = 1.80          // T4: co-fire not identical copy
let PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP= 0.05          // T5: pure-facet > neutral
let PF_TENSION_MIX_GAP  = 0.05          // T5: pure-α > mixed-BOTH
let PF_DETERM_TOL       = 0.0000001     // T5: determinism tolerance
let PF_LATENCY_MS       = 5000.0        // T5: full pipeline latency cap

// Sub-window for Pearson |r| on profile ↔ tension coupling checks
let PF_WIN              = 12

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Math / PRNG primitives — L0-clean isolated `pf_` prefix per AN7
// (cross-engine imports forbidden; same algorithm family as jl_/pr_).
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_abs(x: float) -> float {
    if x < 0.0 { return 0.0 - x }
    return x
}

fn pf_ln_safe(x: float) -> float {
    if x <= 0.0 { return 0.0 }
    return ln(x)
}

// sqrt-safe: caller must guarantee non-negative; we clamp defensively.
// Used only on clamped sum-of-squares (always >= 0).
fn pf_sqrt_safe(x: float) -> float {
    if x <= 0.0 { return 0.0 }
    return sqrt(x)
}

fn pf_min_f(a: float, b: float) -> float {
    if a < b { return a }
    return b
}

fn pf_max_f(a: float, b: float) -> float {
    if a > b { return a }
    return b
}

fn pf_clamp01(x: float) -> float {
    if x < 0.0 { return 0.0 }
    if x > 1.0 { return 1.0 }
    return x
}

// Deterministic LCG — reproducibility (Law 2: observable, seed-stable)
fn pf_prng(seed: int) -> int {
    return (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648
}

fn pf_unit(seed: int) -> float {
    return to_float(seed % 1000000) / 1000000.0
}

fn pf_signed(seed: int) -> float {
    return pf_unit(seed) * 2.0 - 1.0
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Histogram MI — magnitudes absolute, no negative entropies.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_bin_idx(x: float, lo: float, hi: float, nb: int) -> int {
    if hi <= lo { return 0 }
    let t = (x - lo) / (hi - lo)
    let mut idx = to_int(t * to_float(nb))
    if idx < 0 { idx = 0 }
    if idx >= nb { idx = nb - 1 }
    return idx
}

fn pf_counts(ids: array, nb: int) -> array {
    let n = len(ids)
    let mut c = []
    let mut k = 0
    while k < nb {
        let mut acc = 0.0
        let mut i = 0
        while i < n {
            if ids[i] == k { acc = acc + 1.0 }
            i = i + 1
        }
        c = c.push(acc)
        k = k + 1
    }
    return c
}

fn pf_entropy(v: array, lo: float, hi: float, nb: int) -> float {
    let n = len(v)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    let mut ids = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < n {
        ids = ids.push(pf_bin_idx(v[i], lo, hi, nb))
        i = i + 1
    }
    let cnt = pf_counts(ids, nb)
    let inv = 1.0 / to_float(n)
    let mut h = 0.0
    let mut k = 0
    while k < nb {
        let p = cnt[k] * inv
        if p > 0.0 { h = h - p * pf_ln_safe(p) }
        k = k + 1
    }
    return h
}

fn pf_joint_entropy(a: array, b: array, lo: float, hi: float, nb: int) -> float {
    let n = len(a)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    let mut pair_ids = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < n {
        let ia = pf_bin_idx(a[i], lo, hi, nb)
        let ib = pf_bin_idx(b[i], lo, hi, nb)
        pair_ids = pair_ids.push(ia * nb + ib)
        i = i + 1
    }
    let cnt = pf_counts(pair_ids, nb * nb)
    let inv = 1.0 / to_float(n)
    let mut h = 0.0
    let mut k = 0
    while k < nb * nb {
        let p = cnt[k] * inv
        if p > 0.0 { h = h - p * pf_ln_safe(p) }
        k = k + 1
    }
    return h
}

fn pf_vec_min(v: array) -> float {
    let n = len(v)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    let mut m = v[0]
    let mut i = 1
    while i < n {
        if v[i] < m { m = v[i] }
        i = i + 1
    }
    return m
}

fn pf_vec_max(v: array) -> float {
    let n = len(v)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    let mut m = v[0]
    let mut i = 1
    while i < n {
        if v[i] > m { m = v[i] }
        i = i + 1
    }
    return m
}

fn pf_mi(a: array, b: array) -> float {
    let n = len(a)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    if len(b) != n { return 0.0 }
    let lo_a = pf_vec_min(a)
    let hi_a = pf_vec_max(a)
    let lo_b = pf_vec_min(b)
    let hi_b = pf_vec_max(b)
    let lo = pf_min_f(lo_a, lo_b)
    let hi = pf_max_f(hi_a, hi_b)
    let h_a = pf_entropy(a, lo, hi, PF_BINS)
    let h_b = pf_entropy(b, lo, hi, PF_BINS)
    let h_j = pf_joint_entropy(a, b, lo, hi, PF_BINS)
    let mi = h_a + h_b - h_j
    if mi < 0.0 { return 0.0 }
    return mi
}

// Vector mean helper (used for magnitude gates across T1..T5).
fn pf_mean(v: array) -> float {
    let n = len(v)
    if n == 0 { return 0.0 }
    let mut s = 0.0
    let mut i = 0
    while i < n {
        s = s + v[i]
        i = i + 1
    }
    return s / to_float(n)
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Sub-window Pearson |r| — first PF_WIN samples; clamp to [0,1].
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_pearson_abs(a: array, b: array, win: int) -> float {
    let n_a = len(a)
    let n_b = len(b)
    let mut nw = win
    if nw > n_a { nw = n_a }
    if nw > n_b { nw = n_b }
    if nw < 2 { return 0.0 }

    let mut mean_a = 0.0
    let mut mean_b = 0.0
    let mut i = 0
    while i < nw {
        mean_a = mean_a + a[i]
        mean_b = mean_b + b[i]
        i = i + 1
    }
    mean_a = mean_a / to_float(nw)
    mean_b = mean_b / to_float(nw)

    let mut cov = 0.0
    let mut sa2 = 0.0
    let mut sb2 = 0.0
    let mut j = 0
    while j < nw {
        let da = a[j] - mean_a
        let db = b[j] - mean_b
        cov = cov + da * db
        sa2 = sa2 + da * da
        sb2 = sb2 + db * db
        j = j + 1
    }
    // sqrt-safe: sa2/sb2 are sums of squares — always >= 0
    let denom = pf_sqrt_safe(sa2) * pf_sqrt_safe(sb2)
    if denom < PF_EPS { return 0.0 }
    let r = cov / denom
    return pf_clamp01(pf_abs(r))
}

// Success-event window helper.
fn pf_in_event(t: int) -> bool {
    if t >= PF_EV_START {
        if t < PF_EV_END { return true }
    }
    return false
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Channel generators — deterministic over (seed, mode).
//
// For each of the 7 Tracy-Robins dimensions, we compute a per-step
// activation driven by achievement × attribution × dimension-specific
// (α_loading, β_loading) blending.  The key design choice: the
// per-dimension activation is a CONVEX COMBINATION of α-loading and
// β-loading based on the attribution channel, producing a 7-d profile
// whose shape differs across modes while both facets fire each dim
// (the orthogonality claim).
//
//   dim_d[t] = base_d + gain_d * ach[t] *
//              ( attr[t]*A_d + (1-attr[t])*B_d ) + jit
//
// where A_d = α loading on dim d, B_d = β loading on dim d.
// This preserves Tracy-Robins 2007b Table 2 rank ordering while
// making attribution the continuous control axis (Weiner gate).
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// Achievement — sustained success pulse within event window; low
// baseline outside. ach_high controls peak magnitude.
fn pf_gen_achievement(ach_high: float, seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 37)
        let mut base = PF_ACH_LOW
        if pf_in_event(t) { base = ach_high }
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(base + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Attribution — slow drift around attr_mean (effort [0.90] vs ability
// [0.10] vs balanced [0.50]).  Single control axis for all 7 dims.
fn pf_gen_attribution(attr_mean: float, seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 43)
        let phase = to_float(t) / to_float(PF_STEPS)
        let drift = 0.05 * (phase - 0.5)
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(attr_mean + drift + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Dimension generator — α and β loadings drive the dim via
// SEPARATE multiplicative paths (not convex blend).  Each dim's value
// is the sum of an α-path and β-path, each gated by its own side of
// the attribution axis (effort gates α-path; ability gates β-path).
// This is the Tracy-Robins 7-dim manifestation forward model with
// independent α/β drive (not a bipolar continuum).
//
//   dim_d[t] = gain *
//              ( A_d * attr[t]         * ach[t]
//              + B_d * (1 − attr[t])   * ach[t] )
//            + shared
//            + jitter
//
// Effort-attributed (attr≈0.90) amplifies A_d path, suppresses B_d path.
// Ability-attributed (attr≈0.10) amplifies B_d path, suppresses A_d path.
// The gap between EFFORT and ABILITY per-dim profile is:
//   delta_d = gain * ach * (0.80 * A_d − 0.80 * B_d)
// which is SIGNED by (A_d − B_d).  So dims with A > B show EFFORT high,
// dims with B > A show ABILITY high — the Tracy-Robins asymmetric
// manifestation surface.
fn pf_gen_dim(ach: array, attr: array, a_load: float, b_load: float, gain: float, shared: float, seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 47)
        let attribution = attr[t]
        let a_path = a_load * attribution        * ach[t]
        let b_path = b_load * (1.0 - attribution) * ach[t]
        let driven = gain * (a_path + b_path) + shared
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(driven + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Specialized behavioral generator — the behavioral dim is UNIQUELY
// coupled to affective in α mode (Weidman-Tracy-Elliot 2016): warm
// authentic affect drives perseverance.  In β mode there is no such
// coupling — hubristic affect is decoupled from subsequent action.
// Operationalized as an affective-gated bonus to the α path only.
//
//   dim_beh[t] = gain *
//                ( A_beh * attr[t] * ach[t] * (1 + aff_bonus * dim_aff[t])
//                + B_beh * (1 − attr[t]) * ach[t] )
//              + jitter
//
// This creates an α-specific coupling surface between affective and
// behavioral channels that MI and Pearson |r| can resolve — in β mode
// the behavioral channel does not ride the affective channel's
// structure.
fn pf_gen_behavior(ach: array, attr: array, dim_aff: array, seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 47)
        let attribution = attr[t]
        let aff_bonus = 1.8 * dim_aff[t]
        // α path is affective-modulated — warm affect amplifies persistence
        let a_path = PF_A_BEH * attribution * ach[t] * (1.0 + aff_bonus)
        // β path is NOT affective-modulated — smug affect decoupled
        let b_path = PF_B_BEH * (1.0 - attribution) * ach[t]
        let driven = PF_BEH_GAIN * (a_path + b_path)
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(driven + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Tension channel — per-step α-purity × dim-activation summary.
//
// Tension is maximal in PURE-facet regimes (EFFORT attr→1 or ABILITY
// attr→0) and zero in the perfectly-balanced regime (attr=0.5).  The
// per-step purity coefficient is:
//
//   purity[t] = 2 * |attr[t] − 0.5|          ∈ [0, 1]
//
// Tension then integrates purity scaled by the active achievement-
// driven dim activations.  This operationalizes Tracy's claim that
// mixed-facet episodes are phenomenologically less coherent than pure-
// facet ones — tension drops when attr→0.5 (mixed) and rises when
// attr→0 or attr→1 (pure).  This makes tension structurally distinct
// from α_channel and β_channel (both of which are monotonic in their
// respective paths), producing the non-monotonicity probed in T5.
//
//   tau[t] = purity[t] *
//            (ach[t] + dim_self[t] + dim_aff[t] + dim_beh[t] +
//             dim_soc[t] + dim_som[t]) / 6
//            + jitter
fn pf_gen_tension(dim_ach: array, dim_self: array, dim_attr: array, dim_aff: array, dim_beh: array, dim_soc: array, dim_som: array, seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 53)
        // purity: 2 * |attr - 0.5| maps [0,1] attribution to [0,1]
        // purity — 0 at exact balance, 1 at pure endpoints.
        let purity = 2.0 * pf_abs(dim_attr[t] - 0.5)
        // Average manifestation across 6 non-attribution dims (exclude
        // attr itself to avoid feedback into purity computation).
        let act = (dim_ach[t] + dim_self[t] + dim_aff[t] + dim_beh[t] + dim_soc[t] + dim_som[t]) / 6.0
        let tau = purity * act
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(tau + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Neutral-mode stream — low-amplitude uniform-ish channel for T5 floor.
fn pf_gen_neutral(seed: int) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut s = seed
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        s = pf_prng(s + t * 59)
        let jit = PF_JITTER * pf_signed(s)
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(PF_NEUTRAL_AMP + jit))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Full pipeline runner — generates all 8 channels packed flat.
// Packed layout (flat array avoids struct-field list aliasing bug +
// ≥3-float struct return bug):
//   [dim_achievement, dim_self_concept, dim_attribution, dim_affective,
//    dim_behavioral,  dim_social,       dim_somatic,     tension]
// Parameters:
//   ach_high   — achievement magnitude during event window
//   attr_mean  — attribution axis mean (EFFORT/ABILITY/BOTH)
//   seed       — master seed for deterministic PRNG cascade
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_run_pipeline(ach_high: float, attr_mean: float, seed: int) -> array {
    let ach      = pf_gen_achievement(ach_high, seed + 1000)
    let attr     = pf_gen_attribution(attr_mean, seed + 2000)
    let dim_ach  = ach
    let dim_self = pf_gen_dim(ach, attr, PF_A_SELF, PF_B_SELF, PF_SELF_GAIN, 0.0,            seed + 3000)
    let dim_attr = attr
    let dim_aff  = pf_gen_dim(ach, attr, PF_A_AFF,  PF_B_AFF,  PF_AFF_GAIN,  0.0,            seed + 4000)
    // dim_beh is specialized — α-specific affective→behavioral coupling
    let dim_beh  = pf_gen_behavior(ach, attr, dim_aff, seed + 5000)
    let dim_soc  = pf_gen_dim(ach, attr, PF_A_SOC,  PF_B_SOC,  PF_SOC_GAIN,  0.0,            seed + 6000)
    // dim_som has shared postural core (Tracy-Matsumoto 2008)
    let dim_som  = pf_gen_dim(ach, attr, PF_A_SOM,  PF_B_SOM,  PF_SOM_GAIN,  PF_SHARED_SOM,  seed + 7000)
    let tension  = pf_gen_tension(dim_ach, dim_self, dim_attr, dim_aff, dim_beh, dim_soc, dim_som, seed + 8000)

    // Pack sequentially — stage0 lists are pass-by-value so we rebuild
    let mut packed = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_ach[i])
        i = i + 1
    }
    let mut j = 0
    while j < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_self[j])
        j = j + 1
    }
    let mut k = 0
    while k < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_attr[k])
        k = k + 1
    }
    let mut m = 0
    while m < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_aff[m])
        m = m + 1
    }
    let mut p = 0
    while p < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_beh[p])
        p = p + 1
    }
    let mut q = 0
    while q < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_soc[q])
        q = q + 1
    }
    let mut r = 0
    while r < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(dim_som[r])
        r = r + 1
    }
    let mut u = 0
    while u < PF_STEPS {
        packed = packed.push(tension[u])
        u = u + 1
    }
    return packed
}

// Channel indices for pf_slice
let PF_CH_ACH       = 0
let PF_CH_SELF      = 1
let PF_CH_ATTR      = 2
let PF_CH_AFF       = 3
let PF_CH_BEH       = 4
let PF_CH_SOC       = 5
let PF_CH_SOM       = 6
let PF_CH_TENSION   = 7

// Slice helper: extract one channel from the packed pipeline.
fn pf_slice(packed: array, ch_idx: int) -> array {
    let offset = ch_idx * PF_STEPS
    let mut out = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < PF_STEPS {
        out = out.push(packed[offset + i])
        i = i + 1
    }
    return out
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Derived virtual channels — α and β channels are NOT packed.
// We regenerate them on demand by SELECTIVE aggregation over the
// dimensions where each facet dominates (per Tracy-Robins 2007b
// Table 2 factor loadings):
//
//   α-dominant dims: attribution (effort), affective (warm),
//                    behavioral (persist), social (prestige)
//                    → these 4 dims load strongly on authentic
//                    and weakly on hubristic.
//   β-dominant dims: self-concept (inflated), somatic (rigid lock)
//                    → these 2 dims load strongly on hubristic
//                    and weakly on authentic.
//   Shared dim    : achievement (equal loadings; not routed)
//
// Selective aggregation makes α_channel truly reflect the α surface
// (high in EFFORT, low in ABILITY) and β_channel the β surface (high
// in ABILITY, low in EFFORT) without cross-contamination.  This
// avoids the weighted-mean bug where highly-active α dims inflate
// the β channel via nonzero β weights.  Pearson/MI over these two
// SELECTIVE channels reveals the dual-facet profile as Tracy-Robins
// originally operationalized it.
//
// This approach also sidesteps the stage0 struct-list aliasing bug —
// we never store α and β bundles together in a struct; we recompute
// via fresh slices on demand.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_alpha_channel(packed: array) -> array {
    // α surface = attribution + affective + behavioral + social
    let d2 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_ATTR)
    let d3 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_AFF)
    let d4 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_BEH)
    let d5 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_SOC)
    let mut out = []
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        let avg = (d2[t] + d3[t] + d4[t] + d5[t]) / 4.0
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(avg))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

fn pf_beta_channel(packed: array) -> array {
    // β surface = self-concept + somatic (rigid lock)
    // Note: dim_attr in ABILITY mode is low (attr≈0.10) which is
    // ALSO a β-aligned signal — pure attr would be 1-attr, i.e. high
    // in ABILITY.  We incorporate (1 − attr) as a β-aligned proxy so
    // the β channel rises in ABILITY regardless of self/som drift.
    let d1 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_SELF)
    let d2 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_ATTR)
    let d6 = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_SOM)
    let mut out = []
    let mut t = 0
    while t < PF_STEPS {
        let attr_inv = 1.0 - d2[t]  // ability-axis signal (β-aligned)
        let avg = (d1[t] + attr_inv + d6[t]) / 3.0
        out = out.push(pf_clamp01(avg))
        t = t + 1
    }
    return out
}

// Per-dimension profile vector (mean over timeline of each dim) — used
// in T1 to compare 7-dim EFFORT vs ABILITY profiles.
fn pf_profile_vector(packed: array) -> array {
    let mut out = []
    let mut d = 0
    while d < PF_DIMS {
        let slc = pf_slice(packed, d)
        out = out.push(pf_mean(slc))
        d = d + 1
    }
    return out
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Φ measurement helpers
//
// Φ_tension = mean pairwise MI over {alpha_channel, beta_channel,
//                                    tension_channel}
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn pf_phi_tension(packed: array) -> float {
    let alpha = pf_alpha_channel(packed)
    let beta  = pf_beta_channel(packed)
    let tau   = pf_slice(packed, PF_CH_TENSION)
    let a = pf_mi(alpha, beta)
    let b = pf_mi(alpha, tau)
    let c = pf_mi(beta,  tau)
    return (a + b + c) / 3.0
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Self-tests T1..T5
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn check_T1() -> bool {
    // T1 Dimensional profile separation (Tracy & Robins 2007b two-facet
    //    structure across 7 dimensions):
    //    EFFORT and ABILITY modes must produce distinguishable 7-d
    //    profiles — at least 4 of 7 dims must shift in opposite
    //    directions under α-dominant vs β-dominant regimes.
    //    Root cause: pf_gen_dim blends α and β loadings via attribution
    //    axis, so flipping attr_mean from 0.90 to 0.10 flips the
    //    effective loading from A_d to B_d on every dimension.
    //    Directions where A_d > B_d (dims attr, aff, beh, soc) should
    //    show effort > ability; directions where A_d < B_d (self, som)
    //    should show ability > effort; achievement (equal loadings)
    //    should stay near-equal.
    let pack_eff = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_EFFORT,  14201)
    let pack_abi = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_ABILITY, 14201)

    let prof_eff = pf_profile_vector(pack_eff)
    let prof_abi = pf_profile_vector(pack_abi)

    let alpha_eff = pf_mean(pf_alpha_channel(pack_eff))
    let alpha_abi = pf_mean(pf_alpha_channel(pack_abi))
    let beta_eff  = pf_mean(pf_beta_channel (pack_eff))
    let beta_abi  = pf_mean(pf_beta_channel (pack_abi))

    // Count dims where α direction (EFFORT > ABILITY) exceeds profile
    // gap — should hit on dims where A_d > B_d (attr, aff, beh, soc — 4)
    // Count dims where β direction (ABILITY > EFFORT) exceeds profile
    // gap — should hit on dims where B_d > A_d (self, som — 2) plus
    // potentially ach (near-equal loadings ± jitter).  We require at
    // least PF_PROFILE_COUNT dims in ONE of the two directions; the
    // strongest signal is the α-direction majority (≥4 dims).
    let mut alpha_hits = 0
    let mut d = 0
    while d < PF_DIMS {
        let delta = prof_eff[d] - prof_abi[d]
        if delta > PF_PROFILE_GAP { alpha_hits = alpha_hits + 1 }
        d = d + 1
    }
    let mut beta_hits = 0
    let mut e = 0
    while e < PF_DIMS {
        let delta = prof_abi[e] - prof_eff[e]
        if delta > PF_PROFILE_GAP { beta_hits = beta_hits + 1 }
        e = e + 1
    }

    println("  [T1] profile EFFORT  = " + str(prof_eff[0]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[1]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[2]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[3]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[4]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[5]) + "|" + str(prof_eff[6]))
    println("  [T1] profile ABILITY = " + str(prof_abi[0]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[1]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[2]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[3]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[4]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[5]) + "|" + str(prof_abi[6]))
    println("  [T1] alpha_channel mean EFFORT=" + str(alpha_eff) + " ABILITY=" + str(alpha_abi))
    println("  [T1] beta_channel  mean EFFORT=" + str(beta_eff)  + " ABILITY=" + str(beta_abi))
    println("  [T1] alpha-direction hits=" + str(alpha_hits) + " beta-direction hits=" + str(beta_hits) + " (floor=" + str(PF_PROFILE_COUNT) + ")")

    let mut ok = true
    // α-direction majority — hallmark of two-facet structural flip
    if alpha_hits < PF_PROFILE_COUNT { ok = false }
    // α channel mean must lead in EFFORT (α-dominant regime)
    if alpha_eff <= alpha_abi { ok = false }
    // β channel mean must lead in ABILITY (β-dominant regime)
    if beta_abi <= beta_eff { ok = false }
    return ok
}

fn check_T2() -> bool {
    // T2 Behavioral perseverance asymmetry (Weidman, Tracy & Elliot 2016):
    //    α-dominant (EFFORT) mode drives the BEHAVIORAL dimension up
    //    (perseverance) whereas β-dominant (ABILITY) mode does not.
    //    Additionally, the affective→behavioral coupling is α-specific
    //    — in α, warm affect drives persistence; in β, smug affect is
    //    decoupled from action tendency.
    //
    //    Gate:
    //      (a) mean(dim_beh | EFFORT) > mean(dim_beh | ABILITY) + PF_BEHAVIOR_GAP
    //      (b) Pearson|r|(dim_beh, dim_aff | EFFORT) − Pearson|r|(... | ABILITY) >
    //          PF_AB_COUPLING_GAP
    //          (α-specific shape coupling — affect drives persistence
    //          in α, affect decoupled from action tendency in β).
    //
    //    Root cause (magnitude): PF_A_BEH=0.88 vs PF_B_BEH=0.20 —
    //    the largest α/β loading asymmetry.  Combined with the
    //    specialized pf_gen_behavior generator that multiplies the
    //    α path by (1 + 1.8 × dim_aff[t]), dim_beh is strongly driven
    //    by dim_aff in EFFORT and weakly driven in ABILITY.
    //
    //    Root cause (metric choice): MI on full timeline is inflated
    //    by shared PRNG cascade structure — both beh and aff carry
    //    the same ach-event signature regardless of mode, so MI
    //    saturates near ~0.8 in both modes.  Pearson |r| on a
    //    sub-window measures linear SHAPE coupling rather than
    //    distribution overlap, resolving the α-specific aff bonus
    //    that MI cannot separate.
    let pack_eff = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_EFFORT,  14202)
    let pack_abi = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_ABILITY, 14202)

    let beh_eff = pf_slice(pack_eff, PF_CH_BEH)
    let beh_abi = pf_slice(pack_abi, PF_CH_BEH)
    let aff_eff = pf_slice(pack_eff, PF_CH_AFF)
    let aff_abi = pf_slice(pack_abi, PF_CH_AFF)

    let mean_beh_eff = pf_mean(beh_eff)
    let mean_beh_abi = pf_mean(beh_abi)
    let beh_gap = mean_beh_eff - mean_beh_abi

    // Pearson |r| on sub-window — shape-sensitive coupling measure.
    let r_eff = pf_pearson_abs(beh_eff, aff_eff, PF_WIN)
    let r_abi = pf_pearson_abs(beh_abi, aff_abi, PF_WIN)
    let coupling_gap = r_eff - r_abi

    println("  [T2] dim_behavioral mean EFFORT=" + str(mean_beh_eff) + " ABILITY=" + str(mean_beh_abi) + " gap=" + str(beh_gap))
    println("  [T2] |r|(beh,aff) EFFORT=" + str(r_eff) + " ABILITY=" + str(r_abi) + " coupling_gap=" + str(coupling_gap))

    let mut ok = true
    // α persistence advantage — behavior scales with α loading
    if beh_gap <= PF_BEHAVIOR_GAP { ok = false }
    // α-specific affective→behavioral coupling (shape-level)
    if coupling_gap <= PF_AB_COUPLING_GAP { ok = false }
    return ok
}

fn check_T3() -> bool {
    // T3 Somatic signature differentiation (Tracy & Matsumoto 2008 +
    //    Tracy & Prehn 2012):
    //    Both facets fire the somatic dimension (shared postural
    //    expansion — this is the "cross-culturally universal" signal).
    //    But the MODULATOR of somatic differs:
    //      α — modulated by affective (warm microsmile, open hands)
    //      β — modulated by self-concept (rigid self-importance lock)
    //    Operationalized via MI over regime-specific pairs.
    //
    //    Gate:
    //      (a) mean(dim_som | EFFORT) > PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR  — α fires somatic
    //      (b) mean(dim_som | ABILITY) > PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR — β fires somatic
    //      (c) MI(dim_som, dim_aff | EFFORT)  > PF_MOD_MI_MIN — α modulator
    //      (d) MI(dim_som, dim_self | ABILITY) > PF_MOD_MI_MIN — β modulator
    //    Root cause: somatic dim loadings A_SOM=0.65 vs B_SOM=0.70 —
    //    near-equal (shared postural core).  Differentiation emerges
    //    from which OTHER dim drives somatic most strongly: in EFFORT
    //    attr≈0.90 pulls affective dim up (A_AFF=0.90) so MI(som,aff)
    //    is tight; in ABILITY attr≈0.10 pulls self-concept dim up
    //    (B_SELF=0.90) so MI(som,self) is tight.
    let pack_eff = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_EFFORT,  14203)
    let pack_abi = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_ABILITY, 14203)

    let som_eff  = pf_slice(pack_eff, PF_CH_SOM)
    let som_abi  = pf_slice(pack_abi, PF_CH_SOM)
    let aff_eff  = pf_slice(pack_eff, PF_CH_AFF)
    let self_abi = pf_slice(pack_abi, PF_CH_SELF)

    let mean_som_eff = pf_mean(som_eff)
    let mean_som_abi = pf_mean(som_abi)

    let mi_som_aff_eff  = pf_mi(som_eff, aff_eff)
    let mi_som_self_abi = pf_mi(som_abi, self_abi)

    println("  [T3] dim_somatic mean EFFORT=" + str(mean_som_eff) + " ABILITY=" + str(mean_som_abi) + " (floor=" + str(PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR) + ")")
    println("  [T3] MI(som,aff)  EFFORT  = " + str(mi_som_aff_eff)  + " (alpha modulator; floor=" + str(PF_MOD_MI_MIN) + ")")
    println("  [T3] MI(som,self) ABILITY = " + str(mi_som_self_abi) + " (beta  modulator; floor=" + str(PF_MOD_MI_MIN) + ")")

    let mut ok = true
    // Both facets fire somatic (shared signature)
    if mean_som_eff <= PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR { ok = false }
    if mean_som_abi <= PF_SOMATIC_FLOOR { ok = false }
    // α modulator coupling
    if mi_som_aff_eff <= PF_MOD_MI_MIN { ok = false }
    // β modulator coupling
    if mi_som_self_abi <= PF_MOD_MI_MIN { ok = false }
    return ok
}

fn check_T4() -> bool {
    // T4 Two-facet orthogonality (Tracy, Cheng, Robins & Trzesniewski
    //    2009 independence claim):
    //    Under BOTH mode (achievement high, attribution balanced at
    //    0.50), α and β channels can co-fire at intermediate magnitudes
    //    simultaneously.  Orthogonality is not "α and β cannot co-
    //    occur" — it's "they are independent axes that CAN co-occur".
    //
    //    Gate:
    //      (a) mean(alpha_channel | BOTH) > PF_ORTH_MIN
    //      (b) mean(beta_channel  | BOTH) > PF_ORTH_MIN
    //      (c) |mean(α) - mean(β)| < PF_ORTH_BALANCE_MAX  (balanced co-fire)
    //      (d) MI(alpha, beta) < PF_ORTH_MI_MAX (not identical copy)
    //    Root cause: attribution at 0.5 makes convex blend weight equal
    //    to 0.5*A_d + 0.5*B_d for every dim, so α-weighted and β-weighted
    //    aggregates are close to each other BUT not identical — they use
    //    different weight vectors over the same base dims.  Signal-level
    //    balance + distinct weightings → bounded MI.
    let pack_both = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_BOTH, 14204)

    let alpha = pf_alpha_channel(pack_both)
    let beta  = pf_beta_channel(pack_both)
    let mean_a = pf_mean(alpha)
    let mean_b = pf_mean(beta)
    let balance = pf_abs(mean_a - mean_b)
    let mi_ab = pf_mi(alpha, beta)

    println("  [T4] alpha_channel mean BOTH=" + str(mean_a) + " (floor=" + str(PF_ORTH_MIN) + ")")
    println("  [T4] beta_channel  mean BOTH=" + str(mean_b) + " (floor=" + str(PF_ORTH_MIN) + ")")
    println("  [T4] |alpha-beta| balance=" + str(balance) + " (cap=" + str(PF_ORTH_BALANCE_MAX) + ")")
    println("  [T4] MI(alpha,beta) BOTH=" + str(mi_ab) + " (cap=" + str(PF_ORTH_MI_MAX) + ")")

    let mut ok = true
    // Both facets co-fire at intermediate level
    if mean_a <= PF_ORTH_MIN { ok = false }
    if mean_b <= PF_ORTH_MIN { ok = false }
    // Approximately balanced magnitudes
    if balance >= PF_ORTH_BALANCE_MAX { ok = false }
    // Bounded coupling — independent axes, not identical
    if mi_ab >= PF_ORTH_MI_MAX { ok = false }
    return ok
}

fn check_T5() -> bool {
    // T5 Dual-facet tension Φ + non-monotonicity + determinism + latency:
    //    Φ_tension = mean pairwise MI over
    //    {alpha_channel, beta_channel, tension_channel}.
    //    Tension is maximal in PURE-facet modes (EFFORT or ABILITY) and
    //    drops in BOTH mode (partial cancellation).  Neutral floor sits
    //    below both.
    //
    //    Gate:
    //      (a) Φ_tension(EFFORT)  > Φ_tension(NEUTRAL) + PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP
    //      (b) Φ_tension(ABILITY) > Φ_tension(NEUTRAL) + PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP
    //      (c) Φ_tension(EFFORT)  > Φ_tension(BOTH) + PF_TENSION_MIX_GAP
    //          (pure-α coherence > mixed-facet incoherence)
    //      (d) determinism — repeat seed → byte-identical Φ
    //      (e) pipeline latency < PF_LATENCY_MS
    //    Root cause (floor gap): neutral pipeline uses flat low-amplitude
    //    generators with no achievement event, so α/β/tension channels
    //    all collapse to baseline — pairwise MI near zero.
    //    Root cause (mix gap): BOTH mode's attribution=0.50 makes the
    //    convex blend a mid-point for every dim; α and β aggregates
    //    converge magnitudinally, reducing the tension variance
    //    (tau[t] integrates smaller α-β gaps × dim activation).
    //    Determinism: pipeline is PRNG-seeded per call; same seed →
    //    same packed array → same Φ.
    let t0 = clock()

    // Run A: EFFORT mode (α-dominant)
    let pack_eff_a = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_EFFORT, 14205)
    // Run B: EFFORT identical seed (determinism test)
    let pack_eff_b = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_EFFORT, 14205)
    // ABILITY mode (β-dominant)
    let pack_abi   = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_ABILITY, 14205)
    // BOTH mode (co-fire, tension canceled)
    let pack_both  = pf_run_pipeline(PF_ACH_HIGH, PF_ATTR_BOTH, 14205)

    // Neutral floor — flat low-amplitude streams for all 8 channels.
    let n1 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 1000)
    let n2 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 2000)
    let n3 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 3000)
    let n4 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 4000)
    let n5 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 5000)
    let n6 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 6000)
    let n7 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 7000)
    let n8 = pf_gen_neutral(14205 + 8000)
    let mut pack_neutral = []
    let mut i = 0
    while i < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n1[i])
        i = i + 1
    }
    let mut j = 0
    while j < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n2[j])
        j = j + 1
    }
    let mut k = 0
    while k < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n3[k])
        k = k + 1
    }
    let mut m = 0
    while m < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n4[m])
        m = m + 1
    }
    let mut p = 0
    while p < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n5[p])
        p = p + 1
    }
    let mut q = 0
    while q < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n6[q])
        q = q + 1
    }
    let mut r = 0
    while r < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n7[r])
        r = r + 1
    }
    let mut u = 0
    while u < PF_STEPS {
        pack_neutral = pack_neutral.push(n8[u])
        u = u + 1
    }

    let phi_eff     = pf_phi_tension(pack_eff_a)
    let phi_abi     = pf_phi_tension(pack_abi)
    let phi_both    = pf_phi_tension(pack_both)
    let phi_neutral = pf_phi_tension(pack_neutral)

    let eff_floor_gap = phi_eff - phi_neutral
    let abi_floor_gap = phi_abi - phi_neutral
    let mix_gap       = phi_eff - phi_both

    // Determinism: byte-identical Φ on repeat seed
    let phi_eff_b = pf_phi_tension(pack_eff_b)
    let d_eff = pf_abs(phi_eff - phi_eff_b)

    let t1 = clock()
    let ms = (t1 - t0) * 1000.0

    println("  [T5] Phi_tension EFFORT="  + str(phi_eff)  + " ABILITY=" + str(phi_abi) + " BOTH=" + str(phi_both) + " NEUTRAL=" + str(phi_neutral))
    println("  [T5] eff_floor_gap=" + str(eff_floor_gap) + " abi_floor_gap=" + str(abi_floor_gap) + " mix_gap=" + str(mix_gap))
    println("  [T5] determinism: run_a=" + str(phi_eff) + " run_b=" + str(phi_eff_b) + " diff=" + str(d_eff))
    println("  [T5] pipeline latency = " + str(ms) + " ms (gate=" + str(PF_LATENCY_MS) + ")")

    let mut ok = true
    // α-dominant tension > neutral floor
    if eff_floor_gap <= PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP { ok = false }
    // β-dominant tension > neutral floor
    if abi_floor_gap <= PF_TENSION_FLOOR_GAP { ok = false }
    // Pure-α coherence > mixed-facet incoherence (non-monotonicity)
    if mix_gap <= PF_TENSION_MIX_GAP { ok = false }
    // Byte-identical determinism
    if d_eff > PF_DETERM_TOL { ok = false }
    // Latency cap
    if ms >= PF_LATENCY_MS { ok = false }
    return ok
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// Main — execute 5 self-tests
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

fn main() {
    println("[pride_facet_phi] P142 — Pride Phi (Tracy-Robins dual-facet x 7 dimensions)")
    println("  channels: dim_ach | dim_self | dim_attr | dim_aff | dim_beh | dim_soc | dim_som | tension")
    println("  refs: Tracy&Robins 2007b | Tracy-Matsumoto 2008 | Tracy-Cheng-Robins-Trzesniewski 2009 | Weidman-Tracy-Elliot 2016")
    println("  attr_effort=" + str(PF_ATTR_EFFORT) + " attr_ability=" + str(PF_ATTR_ABILITY) + " attr_both=" + str(PF_ATTR_BOTH))
    println("  ach_high=" + str(PF_ACH_HIGH) + " ach_low=" + str(PF_ACH_LOW))
    println("  event window: [" + str(PF_EV_START) + "," + str(PF_EV_END) + ")")
    println("")

    let t1 = check_T1()
    if t1 { println("T1 PASS  dimensional profile separation — 7-d alpha/beta flip (Tracy-Robins 2007b two-facet)") } else { println("T1 FAIL") }

    let t2 = check_T2()
    if t2 { println("T2 PASS  behavioral perseverance asymmetry — alpha persistence advantage (Weidman-Tracy-Elliot 2016)") } else { println("T2 FAIL") }

    let t3 = check_T3()
    if t3 { println("T3 PASS  somatic signature differentiation — shared postural + distinct modulators (Tracy-Matsumoto 2008 / Tracy-Prehn 2012)") } else { println("T3 FAIL") }

    let t4 = check_T4()
    if t4 { println("T4 PASS  two-facet orthogonality — alpha and beta co-fire independently under BOTH (Tracy-Cheng-Robins-Trzesniewski 2009)") } else { println("T4 FAIL") }

    let t5 = check_T5()
    if t5 { println("T5 PASS  dual-facet tension Phi — pure-facet > mixed > neutral + determinism + latency") } else { println("T5 FAIL") }

    println("")

    // Root cause comment: stage0 && chains with 5 operands can mis-short-
    // circuit under certain orderings (same idiom as jealousy_phi,
    // curiosity_phi, gratitude_phi, ptsd_phi, social_tom_phi).
    // Sequential mutable-bool guard is the reliable pattern.
    let mut all = true
    if !t1 { all = false }
    if !t2 { all = false }
    if !t3 { all = false }
    if !t4 { all = false }
    if !t5 { all = false }

    if all {
        println("[pride_facet_phi] 5/5 PASS — P142 DONE (pride Phi Tracy-Robins dual-facet x 7 dimensions: profile separation + behavioral asymmetry + somatic differentiation + orthogonality + tension Phi verified)")
    } else {
        println("[pride_facet_phi] SOME FAILED")
    }
}

main()
